This paper deals with attribute acquisition in ontology using representation learning, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the study of intelligent agents and their behavior. The paper also involves NLP techniques for representing hierarchical classes and attributes, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. The use of ML techniques for learning representations makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for constructing a dataset, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with ontology construction, which involves database (DB) management, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category.
